[30;1m81 | [0m[35m      //[0m
[30;1m82 | [0m[35m      // This implementation requires power-of-two matrices. In order to avoid[0m
[30;1m83 | [0m[35m      // the use of local or shared memory, all index computation has to occur[0m
[30;1m84 | [0m[35m      // at compile-time, since registers cannot be indexed dynamically.[0m
[30;1m85 | [0m[35m      // Furthermore, using recursive templates reduces the mental load on the[0m
[30;1m86 | [0m[35m      // optimizer, since lowering for-loops into registers oftentimes requires[0m
[30;1m87 | [0m[35m      // finagling them with #pragma unroll, which leads to brittle code.[0m

[30;1m2348 | [0m[35m    -----[0m

[30;1m2350 | [0m[35m    al. (KNV) paper [1]_.  KNV relies on rank-1 updates to find the transfer[0m

[30;1m2352 | [0m[35m    rank-2 updates. This yields on average more robust solutions (see [2]_[0m
[30;1m2353 | [0m[35m    pp 21-22), furthermore the YT algorithm supports complex poles whereas KNV[0m

[30;1m697 | [0m[35m    -----[0m
[30;1m698 | [0m[35m    Flat top windows are used for taking accurate measurements of signal[0m
[30;1m699 | [0m[35m    amplitude in the frequency domain, with minimal scalloping error from the[0m
[30;1m700 | [0m[35m    center of a frequency bin to its edges, compared to others.  This is a[0m
[30;1m701 | [0m[35m    5th-order cosine window, with the 5 terms optimized to make the main lobe[0m

[30;1m77 | [0m[35m//! redundant work in order to overlap the latencies of global prefix[0m
[30;1m78 | [0m[35m//! propagation with local computation. As such, our algorithm requires only[0m
[30;1m79 | [0m[35m//! ``~2*n*`` data movement (``n`` inputs are read, ``n`` outputs are written), and[0m

[30;1m21 | [0m[35mdef lsqr(A, b):[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35m    """Solves linear system with QR decomposition.[0m

[30;1m498 | [0m[35m    **Implementation details**[0m
[30;1m499 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m500 | [0m[35m    - At least ``k+1`` coefficients are required for a spline of degree `k`,[0m
[30;1m501 | [0m[35m      so that ``n >= k+1``. Additional coefficients, ``c[j]`` with[0m
